CURTIS LIGHTING CO. v. HILAM Inc. No. 4810. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. June 4, 1934. Ervin J. Youngerman, of Milwaukee, Wis., and Irving E. Hollobow, of Chicago, Ill., for appellant. Casanave Young, of Milwaukee, Wis., for appellee.

Before EVANS, SPARKS, and FITZHENRY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellants, it is now here ordered, adjudged, and decreed by this court that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed, with costs.
